<pb xml:id="p001" facs="oscys.case.0416.015.001.jpg"/>

<div2 type="caption">

<p>To the Honorable the Judges of the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Columbia and County of Washington.</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="body">

<p>The Petition of Rachel Shorter in behalf of herself and her Infant Child Thomas. of Mary Shorter, in behalf of herself and her Infant Child Charles; of Sarah Smith in behalf of herself and her Infant Children Thomas, and Jeremiah; and of William Shorter, humbly sheweth unto your Honors. That your Petitioners are free Persons decended in the direct female line from a free White Woman, and are unjustly detained in slavery by a certain Ann Casanave of the County of Washington aforesaid, as they are prepared to verify. They therefore pray that your Honors will take their case into consideration and that a subpoena may issue to the said Ann Casanave and that your Petitioners may have a trial according to Law and such other process be ordered for their relief as to your Honors may seen meet and proper.</p>

<p>And your Petitioners will ever pray &amp;c</p>

<p>Thomas Randall for Petitioners.</p>

</div2>

<pb xml:id="p002" facs="oscys.case.0416.015.002.jpg"/>

<div2 type="back">

<p>405</p>

<p>Rachel Shorter, Mary Shorter Sarah Smith &amp; Wm Shorter in behalf of themselves &amp; children<lb/>
vs.<lb/>
Ann Casanave.</p>

<p>Petition for Freedom.</p>

<p>Fd 29 July 1822</p>

</div2>

</div1>
    
